    • Method Detail

      • getBitrate

        int getBitrate()
        Bitrate is the value of kbps a voice channel has. Higher kbps means higher voice quality, but it also effects the voice quality to users on mobile or with poor connections.
        Returns:
        The integer value of the bitrate of this voice channel.

      • getUserLimit

        int getUserLimit()
        User limit is the amount of members can be in a voice channel. If the user limit is 0, it means there are no limits.
        Returns:
        The user limit of the voice channel.

      • compareTo

        default int compareTo(IVoiceChannel o)
        Compare this to another VoiceChannel by their integer positions.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<IVoiceChannel>
        Parameters:
        o - The other VoiceChannel.
        Returns:
        the value 0 if the positions are the same; a value less than 0 if this voice channel's position is smaller than the other voice channel; and a value greater than 0 if this voice channel's position is greater than the other voice channel
